post_text: The Board meetings scheduled for August 4th and August 11th will be held remotely via Zoom. Public comments may be emailed to contactboe@sd735.org and will be acknowledged during the meeting, OR you can join the virtual meeting to make a public comment. Please note, after public comments, those attending will be removed from the session to better facilitate the virtual meeting. We encourage those attendees to keep watching via YouTube. The Board meeting will be live-streamed and the link will be posted on the District's website prior to the start of the meeting. Due to technical difficulties, there is no recording for the July 14th Board of Education meeting. We apologize for any inconvenience. The technology department is currently exploring ways to live stream face-to-face meetings going forward that will provide a high-quality viewing experience and reliability.

As a District, we want to acknowledge the protests in and around Chicago, as well as across the country. While the murder of George Floyd is the most recent event, there is a long and painful history of systemic racism, prejudice, and discrimination in our county. Engaging in productive dialogue about how we can support one another and learn from each other, and how we can continue to celebrate the diversity that makes Skokie unique is an important component of community building. In Skokie, you‚Äôve seen the ‚ÄúSkokie Welcomes Everyone‚Äù signs for years. Let us continue to actualize that statement.

We‚Äôd like to share a few resources with you to assist you in continuing to have conversations with your children about race. Our teachers frequently use resources from Facing History and Ourselves, as well as Teaching Tolerance, both of which are referenced in the resources linked on our website. Please click through... https://www.sd735.org/news/1682459/recent-events-060220

post_text: Thank you, Evanston Subaru in Skokie, for your generous support! üôåüèº üòä
shared_text:
Evanston Subaru in Skokie
October 7, 2019 at 4:34 PM ¬∑

Evanston Subaru in Skokie Loves Learning! And as part of the Subaru Love Promise to give back to our community, we donated five boxes of science books to Oliver McCracken Middle School's Library in Skokie, Illinois. Rob and Ray delivered the books to Head Librarian Tori Gammeri and some of her students.

Each October for the past 4 or 5 years, Evanston Subaru has supplied boxes of science books that Ms. Grammeri says have been very popular with all of Skokie School District 73.5 including Meyer Middle and John Middleton Elementary School. Ms. Grammeri added that our educational gifts have been used in the classroom for lessons and also used as prizes for students that excel in contests or science projects.

Rob and Ray delivered the books to McCraken Middle School in an all-new 2020 Subaru Outback.

post_text: Cold weather noises? Here‚Äôs why...
shared_text:
Illinois Storm Chasers
January 30, 2019 at 4:09 AM ¬∑

If you are hearing a lot of loud cracking or booming noises outdoors, they may be because of this:

A cryoseism, also known as an ice quake or a frost quake, is a seismic event that may be caused by a sudden cracking action in frozen soil or rock saturated with water or ice. As water drains into the ground, it may eventually freeze and expand under colder temperatures, putting stress on its surroundings

DNEAL
